## 2. Acceptance criteria

- [ ] `go build ./...` produces a single binary
- [ ] `go test ./...` is green
- [ ] `go vet ./...` is clean
- [ ] `golangci-lint run` is clean (with the agreed config)
- [ ] `/healthz` returns 200; `/readyz` returns 200 only when dependencies are reachable
- [ ] Structured logging via `slog` — no fmt.Println in production code paths

## 3. Non-goals

- No web frameworks unless a hard reason — `net/http` + `chi` (or stdlib `http.ServeMux` post-1.22) is the default
- No `go generate` magic — explicit code over codegen
- No global state — pass dependencies via constructors

